  footnotes: []
english:
  title: Early Dawn
  author: Kim Si습
  language: eng
  text: |-
    Rain fell in the mountains last night.
    This morning I hear the spring water singing over stones.
    The window brightens—dawn threatens to break.
    Birds clamor, yet the guest still sleeps.

    The room is small, and sunlight grows luminous.
    Clouds scatter; the moon lingers in heaven.
    The kitchen master has prepared millet—
    he brings word that tender tea has been steeped.
  footnotes:
  - key: ''
    value: The poem captures a moment of awakening, both literal and spiritual, as the speaker transitions from sleep to consciousness, paralleling nature's own transition from night to dawn.
